<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[19690]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[Reflections on the social impact of taking drugs]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<strong>Exhibitions.</strong> 'Parlem de drogues', at the CosmoCaixa Barcelona, invites you to reflect on drugs and the importance of preventing their consumption in schools.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p class="MsoNormal">The exhibition <em>Let&#8217;s talk about drugs</em>, now on at the CosmoCaixa Barcelona, invites you to think about drugs, the social impact they have, their effects on health and the importance of preventing drug taking in schools. Are we really clued up on the effects of drugs? Can we make up our own minds? What do we really know?</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">These are some of the questions the exhibition attempts to answer and uses to stimulate debate. It forms part of the “la Caixa” Foundation&#8217;s broadest ever programme aimed at prevention, providing information on and raising awareness of the effects drugs have on health and society among the people who are key players in achieving its goal: young people, families, teachers, health centre staff and the general public. The <em>Parlem de drogues</em> (Let&#8217;s talk about drugs) programme aims to stop young people and people in general taking drugs, through an innovative, integrated approach.</p>
